description:
“By this all will know that you are My disciples, if you have love for one another” (John 13:35). 

The greatest evidence that we follow Jesus is our love for one another. When people join or visit our church, what is it that they notice the most? Is biblical knowledge and doctrine the main thing that makes us stand out as Adventists? Is this what makes people want to come back or stay in the church?

This #short clip from the Global #Campmeeting sermon, “The Best Method to Reach the Unchurched” by Pastor Roy Ice of Faith for Today, https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yzE4tyGlZB0&list=PL-k2Gb-DBYo9tb9fHW_AxGxJ1R8MpNnpa&index=36 delves into how our church can become a haven where people love to flock to. 

Watch the video to discover the method God wants us to use to connect with others.
